Quick Notes
C++ is case-sensitive
C++ is a object-oriented programming language
The design philosophy of C++ equates to "trust the programmer"


Terms
IDE   		Integrated Development Environment	  Compiles/Debugs/Executes code
Compiler						  1. Check program for errors
							  2. Convert each .cpp file into an object file (.o or .obj)
Linker							  Combines all object files generated by the compiler into a single executable program
Inheritance						  "is a" relationship
Components						  "has a" relationship


Operators
&	Pointer		Address-of operator
			Read as "address of"
*	Pointer		Dereference operator
			Read as "value pointed to by"


Libraries
C++ standard library


Preprocessor Directives
#include
#include <iostream>
#include "name.h"


Namespaces
Using namespace std


Variable Types
Bool	                  True or false
Char	                  256 characters
Unsigned short int	  0 to 65,535
Short int	          -32,768 to 32,767
Unsigned long int	  0 to 4,294,967,295
Long int	          -2,147,483,648 to 2,147,483,647
Unsigned long long	  0 to 18,446,744,073,709,551,615
Long long	          -9,223,372,036,854,775,808 to 9,223,372,036,854,775,807
Int (16 bit)	          -32,768 to 32,767
Int (32 bit)	          -2,147,483,648 to 2,147,483,647
Unsigned int (16 bit)	  0 to 65,535
Unsigned int (32 bit)	  0 to 4,294,967,295
Float	                  1.2e-38 to 3.4e38 (7 digits)
Double	                  2.2e-308 to 1.8e308 (15 digits)


Syntax/Commands
//	          	  Comment - single line, at beginning of each line
/* and */	          Comment - multi line, on their own lines
Cin			  User input
Cout			  Text displayed to user
	

Functions/Methods
<return type>  <name> (<parameters>)		Function requirements
{
        <statements>
}
Int main()					The only function required for a program to compile
{	
        Return 0;
}
